{"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Building a game is a time consuming and difficult task. You need to bring together many different elements such as visual assets, game play strategy, challenges, and above all the code to bring this altogether. This is where Scroller2d attempts to help accelerate your ideas by providing a framework and visual editor to create levels in a data driven approach that allows you to modularize your game level core logic.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Every level has repeatable core principals: background, floor (horizontal scrolling), enemies, obstacles, collectibles, checkpoints, and artifacts.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Create a Level","level":3,"anchor":"Create-a-Level"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To create a level you can interogate the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Scroller2d\/documentation\/Scroller2d\/Level"},{"type":"text","text":" struct or you can start with LevelEditor to save an initial level."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Upon saving your new level, you will immediately notice a handful of things."}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Every element has a GUID id. This is an internal value primarily used within LevelEditor."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Very few properties are defaulted with a value."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is by design as the majority of the data model is optional, allowing you to decide what your level will look like without being forced to add data indiscriminantly."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Using LevelEditor","level":3,"anchor":"Using-LevelEditor"}